olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 onion
1 carrot
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet pork mince
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Finely chop the garlic and brown onion. Grate the carrot. Drain the sweetcorn (see ingredients). Heat a large frying pan over a high heat. Cook the sweetcorn until lightly charred, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are "popping" out.

Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the pork mince, onion and carrot, breaking the mince up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic and Louisiana spice blend and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture looks dry!

Arrange the mini flour tortillas over a lined oven tray. Divide the pork mixture between the tortillas, spooning it onto one half of each tortilla, then top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Fold the empty half of each tortilla over to enclose the filling and press down with a spatula. Brush or spray the tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil and season. Bake the quesadillas until the cheese has melted and the tortillas are golden, 10-12 minutes. Spoon any overflowing filling back towards the quesadillas.

While the quesadillas are baking, roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. Add the baby spinach, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil to the charred corn. Toss to combine and season to taste. Divide the Southern pork quesadillas between plates. Serve with the charred corn salsa and dollop with the sour cream.